<br>
Ignore that &quot;Vendor Sold&quot; field. It has no relationship to wether or not the spell is actually sold by a Vendor. None whatsoever.<br>
<br>
There are drop-only spells which are Vendor-Sold according to that field (Khura's Focusing, Rod of Mystical Transvergance, Transon's Phantasmal Protection).<br>
<br>
I haven't noticed any current vendor-sold spells that are flagged as 'no' in that field, but I haven't tried all that hard to find one. But, it really isn't much of a stretch to conclude that if some non-vendor spells are flagged as vendor then some of the spells that are vendor available are flagged as not.<br>
<br>
<br>
Vendor-Sold or not can not be reliably determined by that field. Until either PoP is actually released or a PoP Beta Tester choses to reveall the truth (which I presume would be a violation of their NDA), you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> do not know if the spells are going to be on a vendor or not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <p><DIV style="position:relative; width=80%; filter:glow(color=FFFF00)"><h4>Zyphyr Runnersbane</h4></div>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44185">Vending Machine and Disciple of Zomm</a><br>
Darkblood<br>
