<br>
It has been said hundreds of times, but appearently must be said again:  Caster's Realms is very often <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> WRONG</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  Do not trust anything you read there!<br>
<br>
I don't know what happened to Baelish.  When the game first came out, Enchanters were a very strange and misunderstood class.  There was one obscure message board for Enchanters where everyone shared information and tactics.  Baelish was one of the main posters there, and eventually setup the Enchanter's Realm (IIRC, that's what it was called).  It was such a great resource for 'chanters, that other classes wanted their information listed too.  Gradually he added the other pure casters, then priests, then hybrids, and finally melees as well.  Somewhere along the line his bandwidth costs got too high, so he sold-out to pop-ups and banner ads.  After that everything went down hill, he seems to have lost interest with the site, many sections haven't been updated in years, and tons of factually incorrect information has been spewed forth onto the wasteland that was once a reliable and informative site.  RIP Caster's Realm.<br>
<br>
Lucy (the website) and EQCaster (the program) are very good replacements for CR.  You can get news on just about any EQ site, and for where to buy spells look for a class specific site, or try your luck on Allakhazam.<br>
<br>
Ok, back on topic the concept of the jewlery bag <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> rocks!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I hope they figure out a good way to implement it, though. <p><CENTER>
